# SSH Honeypot with Live Dashboard

A fake SSH server that logs every attack attempt and displays them on a real-time world map dashboard. 

## What it does

- Emulates a real SSH server — accepts connections, lets attackers try credentials, denies everyone
- Enriches every attacker IP with geolocation (country, city, coordinates) and abuse reputation score
- Displays everything live on an interactive world map dashboard

## Architecture
Attacker → Fake SSH Server (Paramiko)

↓

Threat Intel Enrichment

├── ip-api.com  (geolocation + ISP)

└── AbuseIPDB   (reputation score)

↓

SQLite Database

↓

Flask Dashboard (live, polls every 5s)

├── World map with attack markers (Leaflet.js)

├── Top usernames chart

├── Top passwords chart

└── Attacks over time chart
## Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Fake SSH server | Python, Paramiko |
| Threat intelligence | ip-api.com, AbuseIPDB API |
| Database | SQLite |
| Dashboard backend | Python, Flask |
| Dashboard frontend | HTML, Chart.js, Leaflet.js |

## Run locally

```bash
# install dependencies
pip3 install paramiko flask requests --break-system-packages

# start the honeypot (port 2222)
python3 honeypot.py

# start the dashboard (port 5000)
python3 dashboard.py
```

Open `http://127.0.0.1:5000` in your browser.

